      <body>(from [48a108d55b6bf50c7960c1c1e10fd1f457fd1ada]) Error message should advice to use 'mysql2' gem.

If I create a new app using command
rails new demo -d mysql
then Gemfile contains 'mysql2' gem by default.

However if mysql gem is missing then error message says
raise &quot;!!! Missing the mysql gem. Add it to your Gemfile: gem 'mysql', '2.8.1'&quot;

